# Publish target for this scope. Kept here (not in package.json's
# publishConfig.registry) so the published package.json carries NO baked-in
# registry — downstream mirrors (e.g. an internal Nexus) can `npm publish
# --registry=<theirs>` without having to strip an override first.
#
# For consumers this line is inert: swiss-function has no @tarassov-ch
# dependencies, so it never changes install resolution. It only steers a
# manual `npm publish` from the maintainer box to code.tarassov.ch instead of
# defaulting to npmjs.com. CI (.gitea/workflows/publish.yml) overwrites .npmrc
# via setup-node with the same scoped registry plus the auth token.
@tarassov-ch:registry=https://code.tarassov.ch/api/packages/ux/npm/
